<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Single specimen. Body long, ~ 3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 47" captionStartId="F47" captionText="Figure 47. Peniagone vitrea Theel, 1882. Specimen CCZ _ 077: A, B in situ images C lateral view before preservation D dorsal view E dorsal ossicles. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 3 cm (B); 200 μm (E). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A, B); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (C, D); Bribiesca-Contreras (E)" figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716373" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">47C, D</figureCitation>
). Mouth anterior, downwards; foremost neck-like part bent forwards in acute angle with ventral surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 47" captionStartId="F47" captionText="Figure 47. Peniagone vitrea Theel, 1882. Specimen CCZ _ 077: A, B in situ images C lateral view before preservation D dorsal view E dorsal ossicles. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 3 cm (B); 200 μm (E). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A, B); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (C, D); Bribiesca-Contreras (E)" figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716373" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">47C</figureCitation>
); with ten tentacles of similar sizes; anus terminal. Velum consists of two pairs processes, fully fused by a membrane forming a lobe, with only the tips free; the two middle processes are much larger (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 47" captionStartId="F47" captionText="Figure 47. Peniagone vitrea Theel, 1882. Specimen CCZ _ 077: A, B in situ images C lateral view before preservation D dorsal view E dorsal ossicles. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 3 cm (B); 200 μm (E). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A, B); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (C, D); Bribiesca-Contreras (E)" figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716373" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">47A, B, D</figureCitation>
). Eight pairs of tube feet surrounding the posterior third of ventral surface, decreasing in size distally. Skin translucent in live specimen (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 47" captionStartId="F47" captionText="Figure 47. Peniagone vitrea Theel, 1882. Specimen CCZ _ 077: A, B in situ images C lateral view before preservation D dorsal view E dorsal ossicles. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 3 cm (B); 200 μm (E). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A, B); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (C, D); Bribiesca-Contreras (E)" figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716373" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">47A, B</figureCitation>
), but white, hard, and brittle after preservation, with numerous calcareous deposits (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 47" captionStartId="F47" captionText="Figure 47. Peniagone vitrea Theel, 1882. Specimen CCZ _ 077: A, B in situ images C lateral view before preservation D dorsal view E dorsal ossicles. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 3 cm (B); 200 μm (E). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A, B); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (C, D); Bribiesca-Contreras (E)" figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716373" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">47C, D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal ossicles with four spinose arms, slightly arched, with mostly two long spinose processes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 47" captionStartId="F47" captionText="Figure 47. Peniagone vitrea Theel, 1882. Specimen CCZ _ 077: A, B in situ images C lateral view before preservation D dorsal view E dorsal ossicles. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 3 cm (B); 200 μm (E). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A, B); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (C, D); Bribiesca-Contreras (E)" figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716373" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">47E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
